    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-13T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="496"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.91256D/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-13T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 13, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. Your despatch 310, October 25. Supplement your <hi rend="italic"
                        >aide-mémoire</hi> with a reference to Article 22 of the Telecommunication
                    Convention signed at Madrid December 9, 1932.<note n="39" xml:id="d496fn39">
                        <ref target="frus1932v01#pg_873">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1932, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 873</ref>, <ref
                            target="frus1932v01#pg_883">883</ref>.</note> Your action is
                    approved.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
